Package: furly
Title: Blazing Fast Concurrent Downloads and JSON Parsing
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R:
    person(given = "Mohammed O.E",
           family = "Abdallah",
           role = c("aut", "cre"),
           email = "melsiddieg@gmail.com",
           comment = c(ORCID = "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-5374-0657"))
Description: Downloads many URLs concurrently using the asynchronous, HTTP/2
    multiplexing multi interface of 'curl', preserving input order, reporting
    per-URL failures, and retrying transient errors with exponential backoff.
    Supports GET and request-body methods (POST, PUT, PATCH) and concurrent
    streaming of Server-Sent Events. A convenience layer parses JSON responses
    with a pluggable, fast backend ('yyjsonr', 'RcppSimdJson', or 'jsonlite').
